with a little bit of magick

Joanna Kim

2023-03-12

My Meme

About my meme

I created this meme with R code in posit Cloud (r studio) using the Magick package. I was inspired to create this meme when I encountered a lockdown online class meme with all different types of students in an online call with a teacher. For my meme creation, I used the format of two stacked images along with text next to the images. Three main elements to why I decided to make my meme with cats and about online classes:

  1. My love for cats (although I’m allergic to cat fur) I ADORE them
  2. Due to the pandemic I started off my first year of university with online tutorials/labs and prerecorded lectures, which reminded me how different it was last year
  3. Starting to miss not having to wake up early to bus to the University of Auckland which now makes me feel like I’m starting uni for the first time going to in-person classes every day
library(magick)

# online class meme

# square one
teachers_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                            height = 317.5, 
                            color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "The teacher:",
                 color = "#666666",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# square two
enthusiastic_teacher_text <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/474x/bf/f5/d0/bff5d074d399bdfec6071e9168398406.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Good Morning Class!",
                 color = "#ffff33",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "south")


# square three
students_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                       height = 375.2, 
                       color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Every student with \n their camera \n and mic off:",
                 color = "#666666",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")


# square four
speechless_text <- image_read("https://static.boredpanda.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/tucked-in-kitties-subreddit-60f941152cfa3__700.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "...",
                 color = "#ffff33",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "south")

# combining the top row
teacher_vector <- c(teachers_text, enthusiastic_teacher_text)
top_row <- image_append(teacher_vector)

# combining the bottom row
all_students_vector <- c(students_text, speechless_text)
bottom_row <- image_append(all_students_vector)

#final meme combined
online_class_meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

image_write(online_class_meme, "online_class_meme.png")

My animated GIF

About my animation

I created this animation with R code in posit Cloud (r studio) using the Magick package. I was trying to get some inspiration for my animation that could be simple, yet still appealing. For my animated GIF, I used four frames using the URL link for four different images and added a border, and included some text around the border. When I asked my peers for some broad ideas I could use to find the animation I wanted to create, I got motive by these suggestions:

  • An animal in the GIF
  • A box with a surprise coming out
  • Easter themed since Easter is coming up
library(magick)

first_image <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1176390869/vector/vector-flat-design-cartoon-style-illustration-magic-black-hat-with-magic-wand-and-magical.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=CLIZyTFH-hBFrt-D_rp-Cq4nGTUHRXCZJjHpUuX_e7g=") %>%
  image_border("white", "50x50") %>%
  image_scale(500)
  

second_image <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1167235346/vector/icon-of-magic-black-hat-with-white-rabbit-bunny-ears.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=tSpJ_OIefmJdoTaJyR7a7basiQiqrdRXivB8gz9-0T8=") %>%
  image_border("red", "50x50") %>%
  image_scale(500)
  
third_image <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1167235374/vector/magic-black-hat-with-sweet-white-rabbit-inside.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=RzGlnObZDri17bOfREkfQNhfjB9jX_cZ_beSwxH6uGY=") %>%
  image_border("white", "50x50") %>%
  image_scale(500)

fourth_image <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1167235336/vector/isolated-cute-and-sweet-white-bunny-rabbit-in-sitting-pose-with-red-heart.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=PiLrBCFpa3s96-SybQH6dqTwjMw8qOgZskrBnlFL330=") %>%
  image_border("red", "50x50") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# creating each frame, with the text describing each frame
frame1 <- first_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "ABRACADABRA", size = 40, gravity = "north", font = "Georgia") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- second_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "???", size = 40, gravity = "northwest", font = "Georgia") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame3 <- third_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "TAAADAA!!!", size = 40, gravity = "northeast", font = "Georgia") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- fourth_image %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating an animation
magic_animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

image_write(magic_animation, "magic_animation.gif")s
